abstract: In the changing suburbs of Bucks County in Pennsylvania, where traditional party allegiances are scrambled, voters viewed impeachment through the prism of President Trump.
snippet: In the changing suburbs of Bucks County in Pennsylvania, where traditional party allegiances are scrambled, voters viewed impeachment through the prism of President Trump.
lead_paragraph: BUCKINGHAM TOWNSHIP, Pa. — Treacy Broadhead, a registered Republican, has voted in recent years for all of her party’s candidates for office, save one: Donald J. Trump.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren has recalibrated her rhetoric on Medicare for All, as concerns about her support for replacing private insurance with a government-run plan continue to buffet her once-surging Democratic presidential campaign.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren has recalibrated her rhetoric on Medicare for All, as concerns about her support for replacing private insurance with a government-run plan continue to buffet her once-surging Democratic presidential campaign.
lead_paragraph: CLINTON, Iowa — Elizabeth Warren has recalibrated her rhetoric on Medicare for All, as concerns about her support for replacing private insurance with a government-run plan continue to buffet her once-surging Democratic presidential campaign.
headline_main: Seeking Fresh Momentum, Democrat Warren Recalibrates 'Medicare for All' Rhetoric

abstract: Real Madrid coach Zinedine Zidane was left feeling disappointed with his side's 0-0 draw at eternal rivals Barcelona in La Liga after they failed to take their chances against the champions in Wednesday's rescheduled 'Clasico'.
snippet: Real Madrid coach Zinedine Zidane was left feeling disappointed with his side's 0-0 draw at eternal rivals Barcelona in La Liga after they failed to take their chances against the champions in Wednesday's rescheduled 'Clasico'.
lead_paragraph: BARCELONA — Real Madrid coach Zinedine Zidane was left feeling disappointed with his side's 0-0 draw at eternal rivals Barcelona in La Liga after they failed to take their chances against the champions in Wednesday's rescheduled 'Clasico'.
headline_main: Zidane Draws Little Cheer From Stalemate
headline_print_headline: Zidane Draws Little Cheer From Stalemate

abstract: One day after House Republicans stood in unanimous opposition to impeachment, Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell positioned his GOP-controlled chamber to second the party's unapologetic embrace of President Donald Trump, putting the president's effective takeover of the party on stark display.
snippet: One day after House Republicans stood in unanimous opposition to impeachment, Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell positioned his GOP-controlled chamber to second the party's unapologetic embrace of President Donald Trump, putting the president'...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — One day after House Republicans stood in unanimous opposition to impeachment, Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell positioned his GOP-controlled chamber to second the party's unapologetic embrace of President Donald Trump, putting the president's effective takeover of the party on stark display.
headline_main: GOP Embraces Trump as Never Before With Anti-Impeachment
headline_print_headline: GOP Embraces Trump as Never Before With Anti-Impeachment

abstract: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of Canada tried to “undermine” his attorney general in the case, according to a top ethics official.
snippet: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of Canada tried to “undermine” his attorney general in the case, according to a top ethics official.
lead_paragraph: OTTAWA — The company whose corruption case nearly derailed Prime Minister Justin Trudeau’s campaign for re-election, bruising his image as a feminist and defender of “sunny ways,” pleaded guilty on Wednesday to a fraud charge of bribing Libyan officials.

abstract: Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon will on Thursday demand the right to hold a new independence referendum, challenging Prime Minister Boris Johnson to keep the United Kingdom together as he grapples with its coming split from the European Union.

lead_paragraph: LONDON — Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon will on Thursday demand the right to hold a new independence referendum, challenging Prime Minister Boris Johnson to keep the United Kingdom together as he grapples with its coming split from the European Union.
